    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Moissanite is naturally occurring silicon carbide and its various crystalline polymorphs. It has the chemical formula SiC and is a rare mineral, discovered by the French chemist Henri Moissan in 1893. Silicon carbide is useful for commercial and industrial applications due to its hardness, optical properties and thermal conductivity. In jewelry it is used as a imitation diamond.</Note_Text>
